params.name: do_resize
params.description: Whether to resize the images (height, width) dimensions to (size[height], size[width]). Can beoverridden by do_resize in preprocess.

params.name: size
params.type: Dict[str, int] optional, defaults to {"height" -- 224, "width": 224}):Size of the image after resizing. Can be overridden by size in preprocess.

params.name: resample
params.description: Resampling filter to use if resizing the image. Can be overridden by resample in preprocess.

params.name: do_rescale
params.description: Whether to rescale the images pixel values by the specified rescale_value. Can be overridden bydo_rescale in preprocess.

params.name: rescale_factor
params.description: Value by which the images pixel values are rescaled. Can be overridden by rescale_factor inpreprocess.

params.name: do_normalize
params.description: Whether to normalize the image. Can be overridden by the do_normalize parameter in the preprocessmethod.

params.name: image_mean
params.description: Mean to use if normalizing the image. This is a float or list of floats the length of the number ofchannels in the image. Can be overridden by the image_mean parameter in the preprocess method.

params.name: image_std
params.description: Standard deviation to use if normalizing the image. This is a float or list of floats the length of thenumber of channels in the image. Can be overridden by the image_std parameter in the preprocess method.

params.name: apply_ocr
params.description: Whether to apply the Tesseract OCR engine to get words + normalized bounding boxes. Can be overridden bythe apply_ocr parameter in the preprocess method.

params.name: ocr_lang
params.description: The language, specified by its ISO code, to be used by the Tesseract OCR engine. By default, English isused. Can be overridden by the ocr_lang parameter in the preprocess method.

params.name: tesseract_config
params.description: Any additional custom configuration flags that are forwarded to the config parameter when callingTesseract. For example: â€”psm 6. Can be overridden by the tesseract_config parameter in thepreprocess method.
